text.tspan: Human rights weighted by population, World
Based on the expert assessments and index by V-Dem. It captures the extent to which people are free from
government torture, political killings, and forced labor, they have property rights, and enjoy the freedoms of
movement, religion, expression, and association. The variables ranges from 0 to 1 (most rights).
Source: OWID based on V-Dem (v12), Gapminder (v6), HYDE (v3.2), and UN (2019).
